examples.en: There are obvious gains for the student.
He gains a hundred a year.
Gains in one area offset losses in another.
He refused to disgorge his ill-gotten gains.
The party made considerable gains at local elections.
It is our duty to fend off a thief from obtaining his gains.
Sell your stocks now to lock in some of the gains of recent months.
Recent elections have shown significant gains by right-wing groups.
The film gains incisive bite from Sellers' performance as the union chief.
Companies are under pressure to trade off price stability for short-term gains.
A woman is looked upon as demeaning herself, if she gains a maintenance by her needle. (S. Richardson)
